# PRODUCTION Caddy config for the discord-clone server.
#
# Caddy auto-provisions and renews a Let's Encrypt cert for {$CADDY_SITE} and
# reverse-proxies everything to the server container. `reverse_proxy` forwards
# the WebSocket Upgrade/Connection headers AUTOMATICALLY — do NOT add manual
# header rules; the /ws gateway (and voice signaling that rides it) works over
# WSS with no extra config. The single proxied origin serves the whole API:
# https://{$CADDY_SITE}  ->  /, /health, /api/*, attachment streams
# wss://{$CADDY_SITE}/ws ->  the gateway + voice signaling
#
# WebRTC MEDIA bypasses Caddy entirely. The UDP range 40000-40010/udp is raw
# DTLS-SRTP, not HTTP — Caddy only handles 80/443 TCP. That range reaches the
# `server` container directly via the compose UDP port mapping and must be
# allowed by the host firewall + UDP-forwarded on the router to PUBLIC_HOST.

# Global options: register the ACME account with the operator's email. Caddy
# still issues certs if CADDY_ACME_EMAIL is empty (just no account email).
{
	email {$CADDY_ACME_EMAIL}
}

{$CADDY_SITE} {
	reverse_proxy server:8080
}
